<b>Posted On:</b> 5:00 p.m. 16/3/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Re: PvP and Dueling....<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1502" TARGET=_self>PvP and Dueling....</A> (Sudoxe)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>> 1) Paladin seems to be a bad choice for Dueling... I do not know

<BR>&gt; why, because they are strong, hard to kill, can heal, root and
<BR>&gt; have the "Holy Swords" (Any infos on them ?). So are
<BR>&gt; they Good or Bad in PvP (duels AND groups) ??
<P>Very good in PVP because you get 2x hitpoints, because paladins can use lay on hands, this gives them a wicked advantage. Yes, they are nice in PVP.
<P>&gt; 2) Nercomancers are known to be strong in PvP... But the spell
<BR>&gt; "Cancel Magic" can be used against all the nerco
<BR>&gt; persistant damages, and the necro have no "Root"
<BR>&gt; spells... So why are they so strong ? Are they the Best, Good or
<BR>&gt; Bad in PvP (duels AND groups ??
<P>Very strong, but cancel magic makes them near useless, but hey you can't cancel a pet :P) Perhaps Verant should tweak cancel magic a bit make it more resistable or something,..
<P>&gt; 3) I really need to play a powerfull duellist PvPer (good in
<BR>&gt; group too), and this char have to be good in solo PvP-... What
<BR>&gt; should I choose ??
<P>Hehe, ...
<P>&gt; 4) Can a warrior type (such Paladin) kill easely a spellcaster
<BR>&gt; once they are in melee ?? Is it easy to flee for the spellcaster
<BR>&gt; ?? Can spells be resisted ??
<P>I fought one with my spellcaster, lets just say they are tough and that lay on hands really shines...
<P>-Tarquin
